  "body": "Hello There Besu developers, \r\n\r\nI am new to Besu and learning besu by myself.\r\n\r\nI forked Besu, build dependencies, ran Besu node. Upto here everyting is fine. \r\n\r\nBut now I started making small changes inside the RPC methods for example adding logs etc. \r\n\r\nSo Inside the rpc method name eth_getBalance, and the file name is EthGetBalance.java. \r\n\r\nI made some changes for logging the request payload. for logging the request payload I used this code. \r\n\r\n`JsonRpcRequest jsonRpcRequest = request.getRequest();\r\n\r\n    LOG.error(\"jsonRpcRequest payload:::::::::::::: {}\", jsonRpcRequest);`\r\n    \r\n  it works fine and I am able to see the logs for my request payload at console.\r\n  \r\n  \r\n![image](https://github.com/hyperledger/besu/assets/89021712/15fae3e3-6f73-4c9e-91af-222afafe34f9)\r\n\r\n\r\nNow I want to log the request header. but I am not sure how can I do so. and looking for some help from some help. \r\n\r\nThanks. ",
